To My Darling Wife.
I am so lucky to have you. You help us to see the best in things. You set such a wonderful example.
You balance us. You are strong when I am weak. You let me help when you can't reach.

You worry about the things I do not. You calm me when I worry and need not.
You accept the things about me that may never change.
Where I can do better at being a Father, you make me face things I would rather not. And I am glad of it. If sometimes grumpy and embarrased.
Every year with you has been different, special and exausting. I doubt that will ever change. And I will love you always.
